        "text": "laurencemcfunk — 23.03.2024 20:40\nAdditional questions building on my question from yesterday: Is anyone really familiar with [[Teapot]]? I am trying to use it to set up my mock server endpoints for testing; and it works for that purpose, but I have two massive frustrations I'm having trouble working around. The first is that it appears I can't bind routes to an instance after I set it up. Well that makes sense, I just have to restart the server during my test setup. However, for whatever reason, Teapot stopAll always returns an error that #stop was sent to nil instead of stopping the server- so I have to open Pharo's process browser and manually terminate the ZnManagingMultithreadedServer.\n\nThis problem occurs when running individual tests, but it does seem to tear down properly when I run my entire test suite class at once. The thing is if I have to run an individual test multiple times, a new ZnManagingMultithreadedServer process spawns for each run, and I have to manually terminate all of them before I can rewrite a mock handler.\nWondering what the proper way to handle all of this is."
